p: For O. basilicum EOs, the obtained results represented in Figure 1 illustrated that the highest significant value of mortality 100% using concentration 6 mg/cm 2 at 48 h exposure time, compared to control (10 ppm malathion), followed by 92.2% at 6 mg/cm 2 after 24 h exposure time. On the other hand, there was no mortality in any of the untreated control.
